  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Livigno</strong></p>
<p>Beginners are very well catered for, the nursery slopes at village level encourage first timers to progress to higher runs. There are easy blues from the top to the bottom of the mountain.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Livigno<br /></strong></p>
<p>Livigno is an Intermediates paradise, with refreshingly few lift queues. Head up the Carosello gondola for a large selection of wide, sunny pistes then cross the mountain to the stunning Costaccia ski area above the old town. Hop on the ski bus to the Mottolino area with its more testing terrain, confidence building black runs and the peaceful, scenic Trepalle runs.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Livigno<br /></strong></p>
<p>Freeride adventures will capture the imagination of the advanced skier.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Livigno<br /></strong></p>
<p>Snowboarders are spoilt for choice! Livigno has two extreme snowboard parks, of which the Mottolino side has been been voted the best in Italy. Whilst known for it's daunting jumps there's a lot fun to be had on the rails, boxes and smaller jumps. Be sure to check what's on in Livigno so as not to miss any freestyle displays. </p>]]></generalInformation>
